2026-05-09 PR #1 merged: `feat(release): canonicalize artifact naming` was merged via squash commit `d861aa4` from https://github.com/SSobol77/ecli/pull/9. The PR added `audit-report.md`, migrated release artifact filenames to `ecli_<version>_<os>_<arch>.<ext>`, aligned Makefile/script/workflow artifact globs, fixed the AppImage script path convergence, updated the normative artifact contract, and made deprecated Projects Classic automation best-effort so CI is not blocked by external board migration. Verification covered `make sysinfo`, `make package-pypi`, contract grep checks, workflow stale-name grep, show-artifact targets, and a Debian 13 AppImage script build producing `releases/0.1.0/ecli_0.1.0_linux_x86_64.AppImage`; GitHub checks were green before merge.
2026-05-09 PR #2 merged: `fix(make): critical release bugfixes` was merged via squash commit `cca38ca` from https://github.com/SSobol77/ecli/pull/10. The PR fixed B1/B5/D6 package cleanup and Snap glob behavior, replaced GitHub release note strings with `--notes-file`, introduced `_ensure-tag` with remote-fetch fallback for tag races, removed the `pip install --user .` side effect from `package-tar-linux`, and added `.coderabbit.yaml` so external CodeRabbit quota failures do not block CI while manual review remains available. Verification covered `make clean`, `make sysinfo`, Makefile greps for six `--notes-file` uses and no stale Snap glob, `_ensure-tag` wiring across all GitHub release targets, a fake-Snapcraft no-output failure proving loud failure, and green GitHub checks before merge.
